{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs-devitem): 23 structured seeds across BtrfsDevItem fields\n\nExisting 14 seeds covered basic-valid + invalid-classes but missed\nseveral boundary classes. Add 23 seeds spanning every parser field\nboundary:\n\n  size boundaries:\n    * truncated 1 byte (well below minimum 98)\n    * truncated 97 bytes (off-by-one short)\n    * 98 bytes (minimum)\n    * 162 / 1000 bytes (parser must ignore tail)\n\n  validation boundaries:\n    * devid = 0 (rejected)\n    * total_bytes = 0 (rejected)\n    * both zero (devid check fires first)\n    * bytes_used = total_bytes (boundary success)\n    * bytes_used = total_bytes + 1 (boundary failure)\n    * total_bytes = 1, bytes_used = 1 (minimum sized device)\n    * devid = u64::MAX, total_bytes = u64::MAX (extreme valid)\n\n  field range coverage:\n    * sector_size 512 / 4096 / 16384\n    * io_align != sector_size (legitimate config)\n    * io_width != io_align (mixed)\n    * generation = u64::MAX\n    * dev_type with all flags set\n    * dev_group = u32::MAX\n    * start_offset large (high 32 bits set)\n    * seek_speed / bandwidth = 0xFF\n    * UUID/FSID = all 0xFF\n    * arbitrary high-entropy pattern across all fields\n\n5.3M runs / 9s post-seed surface no crashes.",
  "files": [
